sec.p:
We use the ESA Radiometric Model [13] to estimate the performances of the ARIEL mission given the planetary, stellar and orbital characteristics: namely the stellar type and brightness, the planetary size, mass, equilibrium temperature and atmospheric composition, the orbital period and eccentricity. This tool takes into account the mission instrumental parameters and planetary system characteristics to calculate:
The SNR (Signal to Noise Ratio) that can be achieved in a single transit;
The SNR that can be achieved in a single occultation;
The number of transit/occultation revisits necessary to achieve a specified SNR;
The total number and types of targets that can be included in the mission lifetime.

The number density (Table 2) and the number of stars are related through (1):
